The accident occurred in Chandler, Arizona.
The accident occurred on December 31, 2012.
The accident occurred at 11:30 Local time.
The aircraft involved was a Cessna 210A.
The aircraft registration was N9507X.
The defining event was loss of engine power (total).

The accident number was WPR13LA078.

The pilot made a forced landing in an open field.
The airplane came to rest about 1/4 mile from the departure end of the runway.
A postaccident examination of the engine revealed no mechanical malfunctions.
A postaccident examination of the engine revealed no failures that would have precluded normal operation.
During a postaccident engine test run, the engine started.
The engine ran for several minutes at various power settings with no anomalies noted.
The reason for the loss of engine power could not be determined.

text:
# Aviation Investigation Final Report

## Location:
Chandler, Arizona

## Date & Time: 
December 31, 2012, 11:30 Local

## Aircraft:
Cessna 210A

## Defining Event:
Loss of engine power (total)

## Flight Conducted Under:
Part 91: General aviation - Personal

## Accident Number:
WPR13LA078

## Registration:
N9507X

## Aircraft Damage:
Substantial

## Injuries:
4 None

## Analysis

The pilot reported that he performed three successful touch-and-go landings. During the fourth takeoff, the engine lost power. The pilot made a forced landing in an open field, and the airplane came to rest about 1/4 mile from the departure end of the runway.

A postaccident examination of the engine revealed no mechanical malfunctions or failures that would have precluded normal operation. During a postaccident engine test run, the engine started and then ran for several minutes at various power settings with no anomalies noted. The reason for the loss of engine power could not be determined.

## Probable Cause and Findings

The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be:

A loss of engine power during takeoff climb for reasons that could not be determined because postaccident examination and testing of the engine revealed no mechanical malfunctions or failures that would have precluded normal operation.

## Findings

Not determined (general) - Unknown/Not determined
